{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Sweep"], "type": "title", "extent": [107, 117], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [117, 194], "text": ["Creates a surface by sweeping cross-sections along a backbone\ncurve."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [194, 521], "text": ["The Sweep op sweeps primitives in the Cross-section input along Backbone\ncurve(s), creating ribbon and tube-like shapes. The cross-section\nprimitives are placed at each point of the backbone perpendicular to it.\nIf a Reference Point input is given, each primitive will be oriented to\naim at its corresponding reference point."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [521, 603], "text": ["The backbone curve can be open or closed, but must have at least two\n  points."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [603, 710], "text": ["If the backbone input has more than one primitive, Sweep will sweep\n  the cross section along each one."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [710, 824], "text": ["If the cross-section input has multiple primitives, you can control\n  them using the ", {"text": ["Cycle type"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [824, 1049], "text": ["Sweep places the ", {"text": ["origin"], "type": "em"}, " of the cross-section on the backbone by\n  default. You can specify a point on the cross-section to attach to the\n  backbone instead with the ", {"text": ["Use vertex"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Connection vertex"], "type": "ui"}, "\n  parameters."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1049, 1200], "text": ["In most cases, you should build the cross section primitives in the XY\n  plane. Sweep will automatically orient them properly along the\n  backbone."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1200, 1341], "text": ["If the backbone curve(s) have point colors or texture coordinates,\n  they will be maintained and applied to the cross section primitives."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "extent": [324, 416], "text": ["Click the ", {"text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SOP/sweep", "scheme": "Icon", "type": "link", "value": "SOP/sweep"}, {"text": ["Sweep"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/sweep", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/sweep"}, " tool on the ", {"text": ["Model"], "type": "ui"}, " tab."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [494, 584], "text": ["You can attach multiple cross-sections to a backbone by selecting more than one."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the cross-section and press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, " to confirm your selection."], "extent": [416, 494], "blevel": 6, "type": "ord"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [657, 740], "text": ["You can select multiple backbones to attach cross-sections along."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the backbone and press ", {"keys": ["Enter"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, " to confirm your selection."], "extent": [584, 657], "blevel": 6, "type": "ord"}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [750, 945], "text": ["You can specify a ", {"text": ["Skin Output"], "type": "ui"}, " from the drop-down menu on the ", {"text": ["parameter editor"], "fullpath": "/ref/panes/parms", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/ref/panes/parms"}, ". However, this only works with ", {"text": ["polygons, NURBS, or bezier curves"], "fullpath": "/shelf/curve", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shelf/curve"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [740, 750]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [945, 986], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/images/shelf/sweep.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "/images/shelf/sweep.png"}]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Using Sweep"], "extent": [294, 324], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": "includeme"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1434, 1544], "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as the cross-section, instead of all geometry in the first input."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["X-Section Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/xgrp"}, "extent": [1387, 1408], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1589, 1704], "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as the backbone curve(s), instead of all geometry in the second input."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Path Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/pathgrp"}, "extent": [1544, 1560], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1753, 1862], "text": ["Only use the geometry in this group as reference points, instead of all geometry in the third input."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Reference Group"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/refgrp"}, "extent": [1704, 1725], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1905, 1942], "text": ["How to sweep the primitives."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Cycle Type"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/cycle"}, "extent": [1862, 1878], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1984, 2024], "text": ["Attempt to fix buckling twists."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Angle Fix"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/angle"}, "extent": [1942, 1957], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2070, 2101], "text": ["Fixes flipped normals."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Fix Flipping"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/noflip"}, "extent": [2024, 2042], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2169, 2205], "text": ["Removes overlapping points."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Remove Coincident Points on Path"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/skipcoin"}, "extent": [2101, 2139], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2264, 2505], "text": ["Tilt the cross-sections towards their respective reference points from the Reference Points input.  The Reference Points input will still be used to roll the cross-sections around the backbone even when this parameter is turned off."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Aim at Reference Points"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/aimatref"}, "extent": [2205, 2234], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2549, 2621], "text": ["Connect a specific vertex of the cross-section to the backbone."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Vertex"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/usevtx"}, "extent": [2505, 2521], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2672, 2720], "text": ["Specific vertex to connect to backbone."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Connection Vertex"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/vertex"}, "extent": [2621, 2644], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [2780, 3176], "text": ["When enabled, instead of using the ", {"text": ["Scale"], "type": "ui"}, ", ", {"text": ["Twist"], "type": "ui"}, ", and ", {"text": ["Roll"], "type": "ui"}, " parameters,\n        the cross-sections are transformed using the backbone attributes: ", {"text": ["pscale"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["scale"], "type": "code"}, ",\n        ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["up"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["trans"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["rot"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["orient"], "type": "code"}, ", and ", {"text": ["pivot"], "type": "code"}, ".  If none of ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["up"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["trans"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["rot"], "type": "code"}, ", ", {"text": ["orient"], "type": "code"}, ", or ", {"text": ["pivot"], "type": "code"}, " are specified, (possibly ", {"text": ["pscale"], "type": "code"}, " or ", {"text": ["scale"], "type": "code"}, " still), the rotation from the curve will be used."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Transform Using Attributes"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "xformbyattrib"}, "extent": [2720, 2752], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3214, 3254], "text": ["Uniform scale of cross-section."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/scale"}, "extent": [3176, 3187], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3292, 3359], "text": ["Cumulative rotation of cross-sections around the backbone."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Twist"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/twist"}, "extent": [3254, 3265], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3395, 3466], "text": ["Non-cumulative rotation of cross-sections around the backbone."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Roll"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/roll"}, "extent": [3359, 3369], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3511, 3554], "text": ["Creates a group for each backbone."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Create Groups"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/newg"}, "extent": [3466, 3485], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3602, 3809], "text": ["Allows naming of the sweep groups. A separate group is created for each backbone by appending a number to the group name. If there is only one backbone, the created group will be called sweepGroup1."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Sweep Groups"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/sweepgrp"}, "extent": [3554, 3572], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [3859, 4534], "text": ["These point attributes and groups will be copied from the backbone points to the cross-section points.\n        If a ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, " attribute is present on both the cross-section and backbone, and ", {"text": ["Cycle Type"], "type": "ui"}, " is set to either ", {"text": ["One Primitive at a Time"], "type": "ui"}, " or ", {"text": ["Cycle Primitives"], "type": "ui"}, ",\n        only the u component will be copied from the backbone, so the v component will still be from the cross-section ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, " attribute.\n        Although only point attributes are copied from the backbone, there is a special case for if the cross-section has a vertex ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, " attribute, point ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, " values can be\n        copied into the destination vertex ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, " attribute, but this only works for ", {"text": ["uv"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Attributes from Path"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "ptattribs"}, "extent": [3809, 3835], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4577, 4669], "text": ["How/whether to create a surface connecting the cross-sections along the backbone."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4682, 4719], "text": ["Do not create a surface."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "extent": [4669, 4682], "text": ["Off"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4731, 4782], "text": ["Skin each set of swept cross-sections."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "extent": [4719, 4731], "text": ["On"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4810, 4880], "text": ["Skin each set and close if the underlying path is closed."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "extent": [4782, 4810], "text": ["On with Auto Close"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4912, 5015], "text": ["Like ", {"text": ["On"], "type": "ui"}, " above, but ensure the swept curves are fully encased in the resulting surface."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "extent": [4880, 4912], "text": ["On with Preserve Shape"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5062, 5136], "text": ["Skin with ", {"text": ["Preserve Shape"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Auto Close"], "type": "ui"}, " put together."]}], "indent": 8, "type": "dt", "extent": [5015, 5062], "text": ["On with Preserve Shape and Auto Close"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Skin Output"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/skin"}, "extent": [4534, 4551], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5178, 5354], "text": ["More efficient skinning. Use when the input geometries maintain\n        the same topologies between cooks and each cross-section has the\n        same number of points."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Fast Sweep"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/fast"}, "extent": [5136, 5152], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5403, 5458], "text": ["Outputs meshes as polygons rather than meshes."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Output Polygons"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/polyout"}, "extent": [5354, 5375], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [1375, 1387], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5485, 5541], "text": ["The geometry to sweep along the backbone curve."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5466, 5485], "text": ["Cross-section"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5560, 5621], "text": ["The curve(s) to sweep the cross-section shape along."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5541, 5560], "text": ["Backbone path"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5643, 5781], "text": ["If this input is connected, each primitive will be oriented to\n        aim at its corresponding reference point in this geometry."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5621, 5643], "text": ["Reference Points"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Inputs", "role": "section", "extent": [5458, 5466], "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "id": "inputs"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5797, 5869], "text": ["Current vertex. It is the current point along the current path."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5789, 5797], "text": ["PT"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5878, 5910], "text": ["Total number of points."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5869, 5878], "text": ["NPT"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5920, 5987], "text": ["Path primitive number. It tells you which path you are on."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5910, 5920], "text": ["PATH"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [5996, 6047], "text": ["Percentage along backbone (path)."]}], "indent": 4, "type": "dt", "extent": [5987, 5996], "text": ["PCT"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Locals", "role": "section", "extent": [5781, 5789], "container": true, "type": "locals_section", "id": "locals"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [6053, 6228], "text": [{"text": ["$PT"], "type": "code"}, " can\u2019t be used to directly index a point in the source, you need to use ", {"text": ["$PATH"], "type": "code"}, " to access the proper primitive, and ", {"text": ["$PT"], "type": "code"}, " the correct vertex in that primitive. "]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [6047, 6053]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6237, 6260], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/rails", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/rails"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6260, 6283], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skin", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/skin"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [6228, 6237], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["Sweep"], "summary": ["Creates a surface by sweeping cross-sections along a backbone\ncurve."], "attrs": {"version": "", "tags": "model, curveup, splines, curves, core", "namespace": null, "internal": "sweep", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/sweep"}, "included": ["/shelf/sweep"], "type": "root"}